<dl id="n41198a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41198a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41198a"> 198(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> taxing his / constitution heavily</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To drink tea from four to six would <mark>tax the constitution</mark> even of a hardened tea drinker! For me, who hardly ever touch it, it would probably be fatal! <font color="green">[L.C. in old age, on invitations to tea.]</font> <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 57</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
